  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nfeature\r\n\r\n**What is the current behavior?**\r\nTo add event handler to components outer layer, it has to be implemented from inside the component as well, like: `return <div onClick={this.props.clickHandler}></div>`  without that can't add event handlers from parent. While something like this should work in my opinion: `<SomeComponent onClick={() => {/*do the stuff*/}} />`\r\n\r\nexample:\r\n\r\n```\r\nexport default class SomeComponent extends React.Component {\r\n...\r\n   render() {\r\n\r\n   /*Doesn't have any event handler logic*/\r\n   return <div>...content</div>\r\n  }\r\n};\r\n\r\n....\r\n/*Isn't working. But in my opinion it should/could as well?*/\r\nrender() {\r\n   return(<div><SomeComponent  onClick={() => {console.log('the click worked!')}/></div>\r\n};\r\n\r\n/*Is working.  Yet I think the last way would be cleaner.\r\nrender() {\r\n   return(<div onClick={() => {console.log('the click worked')}><SomeComponent /> </div>\r\n}\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nSo to sum it up: what I request is that event handler props added to Component would pass on to the outer layer of the Component.\r\n\r\n",
